s attending conferences and symposia  Information on all that Lexington has to offer  including lodging  may be found at the Lexington and Rockbridge Area Tourism site  We encourage guests to reserve hotel rooms as soon as possible   Hotels release their room blocks at various dates in advance of the event  some as much as 30 days out  so by 3 5 some rates will no longer be available    Hotels offering blocks of room for the 2016 symposium  from April 5   April 7  2016  include  Hotel  Rate Per Night   Telephone   Best Western PLUS Hunt Ridge   89 00  540  464 1500 Best Western Lexington Inn   89 00  540  458 3020 Comfort Inn Lexington   89 00  540  463 7311 Holiday Inn Express Lexington   96 00  540  463 7351 Howard Johnson s Inn Lexington  65 95  540  463 9181 Maple Hall Inn  150 00  Some rooms available at the State Rate  Call and Present ID at Check In  540  463 5435 R  E  Lee Hotel   89 00  540  461 8484 Sleep Inn Hotel   Suites  69 00  540  463 6000 Attendees requiring handicapped accessibility or other assistance are encouraged to contact Mrs  Ronda Dove at  540  464 7361 for information and coordination   shuttle service provided VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 